{
  "doc_id": "40062",
  "text": "Non-Hodgkin lymphomas (NHL) are malignancies that originate in lymphoid tissue and arise from T cells, B cells, and natural killer (NK) cells, with MALTs representing only 5% of all NHL [CITATION_1] . The etiology of NHL is poorly understood; however, the most significant risk factor for development of all NHL is immunodeficiency [CITATION_2] . Interestingly, MALT lymphomas specifically have been associated with robust, prolonged inflammation in the case of Helicobacter pylori infection and with chronic immune system dysregulation in the case of Sjögren's syndrome and Hashimoto's thyroiditis [CITATION_3] [6] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
